I"*<h2 id="collapsible-markdown-works">Collapsible markdown works</h2>

<ul>
  <li>You need a <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">markdown="1"</code> attribute in the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">details</code> tag and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">markdown="span"</code> <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">in the </code>summary` tag</li>
  <li>Hat tip to the folks who found this in github.com issue: <a href="https://github.com/github/docs/issues/32988">Update docs for “Organizing information with collapsed sections” to include GitHub Pages support #32988</a></li>
</ul>

<details>
  <summary>Click me</summary>
  <h3 id="yes-even-collapsed-code-blocks-work">yes, even collapsed code blocks work</h3>
  <div class="language-python highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="k">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s">"hello world!"</span><span class="p">)</span>
</code></pre></div>  </div>
</details>

<h3 id="full-code-from-issue-32988">Full code from issue 32988</h3>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>&lt;details markdown="1"&gt;

&lt;summary markdown="span"&gt;Tips for collapsed sections&lt;/summary&gt;

### You can add a header

You can add text within a collapsed section. 

You can add an image or a code block, too.

```ruby
   puts "Hello World"
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>&lt;/details&gt;</p>

<p>```</p>

